{
  "info": {
    "name": "Secure File Delivery API - Azure AD",
    "description": "Postman collection for Secure File Delivery API with Azure AD authentication using **Authorization Code flow**.\n\n🔐 **SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:**\n\n**Step 1: Configure OAuth 2.0 at the COLLECTION level**\n\n1. Click on the collection name\n2. Go to the **Authorization** tab\n3. Configure as follows:\n\n| Setting | Value |\n|---------|-------|\n| Type | OAuth 2.0 |\n| Add auth data to | Request Headers |\n| Grant Type | Authorization Code |\n| Callback URL | https://oauth.pstmn.io/v1/callback |\n| Auth URL | https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenant_id}}/oauth2/v2.0/authorize |\n| Access Token URL | https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenant_id}}/oauth2/v2.0/token |\n| Client ID | {{client_id}} |\n| Client Secret | (LEAVE BLANK) |\n| Scope | {{scope_prefix}}/statement.read {{scope_prefix}}/statement.create {{scope_prefix}}/statement.delete offline_access |\n| Client Authentication | Send as Basic Auth header |\n\n**Step 2: Get Token**\n\n4. Click 'Get New Access Token'\n5. Sign in with your Azure AD user account\n6. Click 'Use Token'\n\n**Step 3: Test**\n\n7. Send any request - the token will be automatically included\n\n**Prerequisites (already configured):**\n- ✅ Delegated permissions: statement.read, statement.create, statement.delete\n- ✅ Redirect URI: https://oauth.pstmn.io/v1/callback\n- ✅ Allow public client flows: Enabled\n\n**Why this works:**\n- Authorization Code flow includes user login → token contains 'scp' claim\n- Spring Boot automatically adds 'SCOPE_' prefix to scopes\n- Your @PreAuthorize('hasAuthority('SCOPE_statement:read')') will match",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8093" },
    { "key": "api_path", "value": "/api/v1/statements" },
    { "key": "tenant_id", "value": "a7048452-8647-45be-a810-e2f665115655" },
    { "key": "client_id", "value": "a3704500-c79d-43b4-a2bd-30b1437e819a" },
    { "key": "scope_prefix", "value": "api://a3704500-c79d-43b4-a2bd-30b1437e819a" },
    { "key": "bearer_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "statement_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "download_token", "value": "" }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{bearer_token}}" }]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "exec": [
          "// Pre-request check for token",
          "if (!pm.environment.get('bearer_token')) {",
          "    console.log('⚠️ No bearer token found.');",
          "    console.log('Please configure OAuth 2.0 in the Authorization tab and get a token.');",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "🔐 OAuth 2.0 Token Setup (READ THIS FIRST)",
      "description": "**To get a token that works with your controller:**\n\n1. Go to the **COLLECTION Authorization tab** (not individual request)\n2. Set Type to **OAuth 2.0**\n3. Configure:\n   - Grant Type: **Authorization Code**\n   - Callback URL: `https://oauth.pstmn.io/v1/callback`\n   - Auth URL: `https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenant_id}}/oauth2/v2.0/authorize`\n   - Access Token URL: `https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenant_id}}/oauth2/v2.0/token`\n   - Client ID: `{{client_id}}`\n   - Client Secret: **(leave empty)**\n   - Scope: `{{scope_prefix}}/statement.read {{scope_prefix}}/statement.create {{scope_prefix}}/statement.delete offline_access`\n   - Client Authentication: `Send as Basic Auth header`\n\n4. Click **Get New Access Token**\n5. Sign in with your Azure AD user account\n6. Click **Use Token**\n\n**The token will now contain the 'scp' claim with your delegated permissions!**",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/actuator/health", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["actuator", "health"] },
        "auth": { "type": "noauth" }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "🏥 Health Check",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Actuator Health (Public - No Auth)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/actuator/health", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["actuator", "health"] },
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Health check returns 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Status is UP', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('UP');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Swagger UI (Public - No Auth)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/swagger-ui/index.html", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["swagger-ui", "index.html"] },
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "📄 Statements (Requires Bearer Token)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. List Statements (SCOPE_statement:read required)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}?customerId=CUST-001&limit=10&offset=0",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "customerId", "value": "CUST-001" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "10" },
                { "key": "offset", "value": "0" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('List returns 200 or 404', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.test('Response has items array', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(json.items).to.be.an('array');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Upload Statement (SCOPE_statement:create required)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                { "key": "file", "type": "file", "src": "", "description": "Select a PDF file" },
                { "key": "customerId", "value": "CUST-001", "type": "text" },
                { "key": "statementDate", "value": "2026-04-01T00:00:00", "type": "text" },
                { "key": "statementType", "value": "MONTHLY", "type": "text" },
                { "key": "accountNumber", "value": "1234567890", "type": "text" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Upload returns 201 or 403', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([201, 403]);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('statement_id', json.id);",
                  "    console.log('✅ Saved statement_id: ' + json.id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Find Statement by ID (SCOPE_statement:read required)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}/{{statement_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"], "path": ["{{statement_id}}"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Find returns 200 or 404', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 404]);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Generate Download Link (SCOPE_statement:create required)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}/{{statement_id}}/download-links", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"], "path": ["{{statement_id}}", "download-links"] },
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"expiresInHours\": 24,\n  \"maxDownloads\": 3\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Download link returns 201 or 403', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([201, 403]);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    var url = json.downloadUrl;",
                  "    var token = url.substring(url.lastIndexOf('/') + 1);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('download_token', token);",
                  "    console.log('✅ Saved download_token: ' + token);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "5. Download PDF (Public - No Auth Required)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}/download/{{download_token}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"], "path": ["download", "{{download_token}}"] },
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "description": "No JWT required — HMAC-signed token provides authentication"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Download returns 200 or 404', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    pm.test('Content-Type is PDF', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/pdf');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "6. Delete Statement (SCOPE_statement:delete required)",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}/{{statement_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"], "path": ["{{statement_id}}"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Delete returns 204 or 403', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([204, 403]);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "❌ Negative Tests",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "No Token - Returns 401",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}?customerId=CUST-001&limit=10&offset=0", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"], "query": [{ "key": "customerId", "value": "CUST-001" }, { "key": "limit", "value": "10" }, { "key": "offset", "value": "0" }] },
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Returns 401 Unauthorized', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Invalid Token - Returns 401",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}?customerId=CUST-001&limit=10&offset=0", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"], "query": [{ "key": "customerId", "value": "CUST-001" }, { "key": "limit", "value": "10" }, { "key": "offset", "value": "0" }] },
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "invalid.token.value" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Invalid token returns 401', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Find with invalid UUID - Returns 400",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}/not-a-uuid", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"], "path": ["not-a-uuid"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Returns 400 for invalid UUID', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(400);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Find non-existent statement - Returns 404",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"], "path": ["00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Returns 404 for non-existent', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(404);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Download with invalid token - Returns 404",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_path}}/download/invalid-token-value", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_path}}"], "path": ["download", "invalid-token-value"] },
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Returns 400/404 for invalid token', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([400, 404]);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}